I had the great privilege to assistant direct and edit this beautiful music video by my dear friend @ashermossofficial . It’s a gorgeous dance piece featuring @emekasimmons and @jasminealbuquerquecroissant

One of the highlights of my work life this year was this shoot with @royalandtheserpent this summer. We shot 4 music videos in 2 days in my hometown of Reno, NV. Royal was adamant about shooting at a real high school and having a consistent narrative thread throughout all 4 videos. Considering schools are some of the more expensive locations in LA, I came up with an exciting but ambitious idea to bring the crew to Reno. The town allowed us to stretch our dollar in ways I have only dreamed of and offered us a huge array of locations.

It was an incredibly rewarding experience to bring my work home and share it with my family and friends. I have always dreamed of shooting in Reno and have a script in development that I intend to shoot there so this was a fun opportunity to explore those possibilities. I want to thank all my family and Reno community for all the favors and hustle that was pulled off.

I was also on camera for the first time in 7 or 8 years which was quite fun. I put more passion and effort into these videos than anything in quite some time and I became personally invested in the opportunity to world build across 4 videos and am really proud of this work. I have been so busy this year I barely got to posting anything about them, so if you have a chance to visit my website and give them a watch that would be greatly appreciated. Watch them in order 1-4 for the full experience.
